@node "Hardware" "The ParKeyboard Hardware"

@{MS "The ParKeyboard Hardware"}

The hardware is very simple. You only need a box, a PS/2 or DIN connector and a SUB-D 25 Plug.
@{"Here" link "/Pictures/Hardware.ilbm/MAIN"} is a small schematic.@{par}

I used a "SUB-D 25 -> SUB-D 9" interface box. If you bend the pins, a MiniDin6 connector for print
mounting is fitting perfect. Just put it in laying on one side. Use hot glue to fix the connector
position.@{par}

Here a list of the requirec connections:@{par}

Sub-D 25           MiniDin6         Din 5@{par}

11            -      1       -     2@{par}

12            -      5       -     1@{par}

14            -      4       -     5@{par}

18-22         -      3       -     4@{par}


@endnode

