@node "NoReset" "ParKeyboard Setup: NoReset"

@{MS "NoReset"}

This option allows to disable the keyboard reset (Control, Amiga, Amiga). When pressing the reset
combination nothing happens at all.@{par}

Some keyboards like A500, A1000 and very old A2000 versions didn't allow to reset at all, because
ParKeyboard is using the ResetWarning key code for reset detection. The most keyboards even the
@{"MMKeyboard" link "OtherPRGS"} are supporting the reset process.@{par}

